SIMPLE: anglo-catholic
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Anglo-Catholic
<hw>An"glo-Cath"o*lic</hw>, <pos>a.</pos>, <def>Of or pertaining to a
church modeled on the English Reformation; Anglican; -- sometimes
restricted to the ritualistic or High Church section of the Church of
England.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Anglo-Catholic</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Anglo-Catholic
<hw>An"glo-Cath"o*lic</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A member of the Church of
England who contends for its catholic character; more specifically, a
High Churchman.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Anglo-Catholicism</ent>⟦br⟧
